	<div class="container">
		<h3>MealPlanning C Prototype</h3>
		<p id="userName">
		</p>
		<h5><strong> Give us in a word or two what you'd like to eat today, and we'll match you with a recipe. </strong></h5>
		<input id="query" type="text" placeholder="i.e. burger, sandwich, ...">

		<h5> Note: the following questions are all optional. </h5>
		<h5> Do you want a specific cuisine today? </h5>
		<input id="cuisine" type="text" placeholder="i.e. american, indian, ...">
		<h5> Do you want a calorie limit? If so, put in the number of calories you'd like to keep the meal to.</h5>
		<input id="calories" type="text" placeholder="i.e. 1200">
		<h5> Any cravings for specific ingredients? You can put in multiple with commas in between. </h5>
		<input id="ingredients" type="text" placeholder="i.e. lettuce, pickles, ...">
		<div class="wrapper">
			<button id="go" type="button" class="btn btn-success">Go!</button>
		</div>
		<div id="after">
		</div>
		<div id="randomRecipe">
			<button display="none" id="nextRecipe" type="button" class="btn btn-default">
				Not exactly what you wanted? Click me for another recipe!
			</button>
		</div>
	</div>

